Status glyphs for the SVG status-pill examples (../battery_svg.py, ../wifi.py,
and the ethernet/bluetooth siblings).

Self-drawn for veiland and released under CC0-1.0 (Creative Commons public
domain dedication, https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/). No
third-party assets are included, so redistribution inside this GPL-3.0-or-later
repository is unencumbered -- copy, modify, and ship them freely.

Each file is a square (viewBox="0 0 24 24") monochrome-white glyph with no text,
fonts, or external references, so librsvg renders it with nothing beyond the
library itself.

battery-25/50/75/100.svg share one battery shell and differ only in the inner
fill-bar width; battery-charging.svg swaps the fill bar for a bolt.

wifi-0/25/50/75/100.svg share one three-arc fan over a dot and light more arcs
as the bucket rises (unlit arcs are dimmed, not removed, so the level reads at a
glance); wifi-75 thins its outer arc the way battery-75 narrows its fill-bar, so
75 and 100 stay distinct. wifi-off.svg dims the whole fan and adds a slash.

ethernet-up/down.svg use the "wired network" motif (a top node feeding two lower
nodes over a bus, as in GNOME's network-wired). ethernet-up is the solid glyph;
ethernet-down dims it and adds a slash, the same disabled-state convention as
wifi-off.

bluetooth-on/off/connected.svg share the bluetooth rune. bluetooth-on is the
plain rune; bluetooth-connected adds two link dots flanking it; bluetooth-off
dims the rune and adds a slash, matching wifi-off / ethernet-down.
